 of promising\ninsulating materials as candidate substrates for graphene to demonstrate such\neffects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Jun 2022 04:44:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 Jun 2022 01:52:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2023 15:44:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-02"}
{"id":"2206.05660","submitter":"Takao Komatsu","authors":"Takao Komatsu and Haotian Ying","title":"The $p$-Frobenius and $p$-Sylvester numbers for Fibonacci and Lucas\n  triplets","comments":"Mathematical Biosciences and Engineering","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO math.NT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we study a certain kind of generalized linear Diophantine\nproblem of Frobenius. Let $a_1,a_2,\\dots,a_l$ be positive integers such that\ntheir greatest common divisor is one. For a nonnegative integer $p$, denote the\n$p$-Frobenius number by $g_p(a_1,a_2,\\dots,a_l)$, which is the largest integer\nthat can be represented at most $p$ ways by a linear combination with\nnonnegative integer coefficients of $a_1,a_2,\\dots,a_l$. When $p=0$,\n$0$-Frobenius number is the classical Frobenius number. When $l=2$,\n$p$-Frobenius number is explicitly given. However, when $l=3$ and even larger,\neven in special cases, it is not easy to give the Frobenius number explicitly,\nand it is even more difficult when $p>0$, and no specific example has been\nknown. However, very recently, we have succeeded in giving explicit formulas\nfor the case where the sequence is of triangular numbers or of repunits for the\ncase where $l=3$. In this paper, we show the explicit formula for the Fibonacci\ntriple when $p>0$. In addition, we give an explicit formula for the\n$p$-Sylvester number, that is, the total number of nonnegative integers that\ncan be represented in at most $p$ ways. Furthermore, explicit formulas are\nshown concerning the Lucas triple.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Jun 2022 04:54:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2022 17:47:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2022 11:01:33 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 21 Nov 2022 10:35:59 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 4 Dec 2022 01:56:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-06"}
